ad_creative_link_descriptions:
She Past Away is a Turkish dark wave/post-punk duo consisting of Volkan Caner (vocals, guitars, and songwriting) and Doruk Ozturkcan (drums, synths, and production). With their haunting sound and minimalist poetry sung in Turkish, the band has established itself as one of the most influential and successful acts in the genre. Their critically acclaimed albums "Belirdi Gece," "Narin Yalnızlık," and "Disko Anksiyete" feature a one-of-kind blend of synth and guitar-driven music, while their dynamic live performances have earned them a devoted following worldwide.

Come to listen live Crime & the City Solution 's first LP in over a decade - inspired by work delivering aid programmes, the album looks at the conflict manifests in everyday life.

TICKETS
bit.ly/F2_LIVE_CRIME_THE_CITY_SOLUTION
ad_creative_link_captions: F2 LIVE: Crime & The City Solution
ad_creative_link_descriptions:
Originally formed in 1977 by Simon Bonney, then disbanded in 1979, a new version was formed in 1985 including members of the recently deceased Birthday Party. With only one record since then, Simon has put together a new Solution with a brand new record out on Mute on vinyl, CD and download on October 20th 2023. The album was recorded in Berlin. Core members Simon Bonney and Bronwyn Adams were joined by Frederic Lyenn (Piano, Bass, Synth), Donald Baldie (Guitar), Georgio Valentino (Synth, Guitar), Chris Hughes (Drums, Percussion) and Joshua Murphy (Piano, Guitar), and for the first time they worked with a producer, Martin J. Fiedler, who also added Synth and Mellotron to the album. Expect cinematic post punk, gothic country and rough blues rockers. Expect melancholy, joy and sadness. 

Supporting we have Joshua Murphy (Crime & the City Solution) who's debut EP Lowlands crafts an almost Nick Cave sound, both somber and atmospheric in his storytelling. Beautiful music indeed.

ad_creative_link_descriptions:
On Friday 16th of June, we are teaming up with Jupiter4, an experimental music label and collective based in Berlin. After last year's explosive concert at Bike_Jesus, we are super excited to welcome Catnapp on the F2 main stage. Favoring emotional expressionism and intense beats, Catnapp is pushing the boundaries of electronic music with a one-of-kind and bold take on songwriting and production.  Especially her live performances have gained wide notoriety. She has been described as „in your face and infectious, conveying the sexual agency and speedy urgency of Berlin’s techno scene while also containing elements of post-punk and rap – something that really comes to the forefront when she performs live.“ 

Joining her will be Jupiter4 co-founder DJ LOUI FROM Jupiter4, Paris-based producer & DJ Simo Cell, who is affiliated with English imprints such as Livity Sound, Timedance and Wisdom Teeth, and the mighty local gang consisting of our resident & slay mama of deconstructed&fast sound NEW MAGIC MEDIA, music enthusiast FFFHHH, and bass boy Kobayashi Maru.

The Take Off KIKI BALL by Mother Monina, Father Michal, Princess Valentýna Ambitchous & FUCHS2 & Queer Spaces Network

Get your vacation mood on for one night and join The Take Off Kiki Ball, provided by Ambitchous Airlines. Fasten your seatbelts, because we're gonna slay the runway to keep ya'll flying high all night long. This flight has zero emissions.

INFO FOR SPECTATORS:
♡ Ballroom is mainly addressing people who identify as LGBTQIA+. The Ballroom is an inclusive space and all bodies are welcome to join and celebrate, but we expect sensitivity, awareness, and allyship for the community, both in and out of the Ballroom. There is no space for any forms of racism, sexism, transphobia, homophobia, misogyny, or any other form of discrimination.
♡ Photography and videography are strictly prohibited during the Body and Sxx siren categories.
♡ Everybody is welcome to join and watch the ball. You can cheer for the performers, you can dance to the beat, you can express your joy however you want to, but please do not enter the stage if you are not ready for it! 
♡ There are no rules regarding your outfit – no dress code nor specific expectations. But if you feel like it, the ball is the right place to go wild. Feel yourself and bring some eleganza extravaganza!

★★★★★ CATEGORIES ★★★★★

★ EUROPEAN RUNWAY OTA, 1 GP: Business class 
Show us your elegance, show us your success. Dress to impress in an outfit that screams "I could buy my own private jet". We want to see the confidence and sophistication in every step you take.
Mandatory: 10s with the suitcase (suitcase on wheels will be provided by organizers, or bring your own if you want to)

★ ALL AMERICAN RUNWAY OTA, 1 GP: Pilot
Uniforms can be sexy, and we want to see your twist on it! Strut your confident masculine walk in your own version of a pilot's uniform. Remember: our lives are in your hands.
Mandatory: Aviator Sunglasses 

★ BEST DRESSED OTA, 1 GP: Traveling low budget 
Traveling with only one tiny carry-on bag means only one thing: layers on layers on layers. Create an amazing, runway-worthy outfit through over-the-top and creative layering. This flight might be sweaty!
Mandatory: Tiny bag

★ BEST DRAG LOOK OTA, 1 GP: Duty Free
The hours at the airport seem like eternity and Duty Free Shop is the only source of joy left. Show us that you've tried it all - from different shades of lipstick and dozens of perfumes to cosmetic samples, chocolates, booze, souvenirs and travel pillows.  Be the draggiest version of Duty Free addict. We want to see something unexpected!

★ FACE OTA, 1 GP: Celebrity incognito
You are a world-famous celebrity! Wear a stylish yet ordinary outfit that's perfect for a superstar incognito. Don't forget to cover your features with a sleek pair of sunglasses, an elegant mask, or any other chic prop – the reveal for your 10s is mandatory!

★ BODY OTA, 1 GP: Survivor
You're the only survivor of an imaginary plane crash. Most of your clothing has been lost. But there's one thing that has emerged unscathed: your amazing body, without a scratch to be found. Are you ready to show off your survivor skills and rock that beautiful body of yours?

★ SxX SIREN OTA, 1 GP: Water landing 
When you're as hot as you are, even flying can be a dangerous affair. In a twist of fate, the plane had to make an emergency landing on the water. Embrace your sexy wet look and let your sex-appeal shine.
Mandatory: Something inflatable

★ REALNESS FQ, TM, BQ, 3 GP: Vacation mode
Get ready to experience the ultimate vacation. Show us that you're ready to kick back and relax by wearing your favorite sunglasses, comfiest flip flops, or the most dangerous crop top. We want to see that you're truly ready to enjoy your holiday!

★ BEGINNERS PERFORMANCE OTA, 1 GP: Fear of flying
You can do this. It's natural to feel a bit nervous – after all, the first time is always the hardest, but with each passing moment, you'll feel your confidence grow as you move your body with ease. So go ahead, step onto the runway and fly! And remember: the life vest is under your seat. 
Mandatory: Vest

★ VOGUE FEM, FF, BQ, 2 GP:  Steward*ess
Who says safety has to be boring? At our Ambitchous airlines, we believe that even the most routine procedures can be spiced up with a little bit of fun and cunty charm. Bring your best steward*ess-inspired outfit and the ultimate accessory – a cute and colorful scarf. And don't forget to incorporate some iconic moves into your performance.

★ POP DIP AND SPIN OTA, 1 GP: Comfy travels 
Ah, the airport - a place of endless waiting, long lines, and uncomfortable seats. Forget about trying to squeeze into your skinny jeans or suffering through a flight in your stiff business attire. The only way to truly feel comfortable (and cool) is by embracing the oh-so-trendy world of tracksuits. Keep it comfy! 

★ NEW WAY OTA, 1 GP: Snakes on a Plane
Are you ready to bring the thrill of the infamous movie "Snakes on a Plane" by David R. Ellis to life? Get your blood pumping with your deadly moves and stretches, in an all green outfit. Embrace your inner snake charmer and make sure to include at least one item in a striking snake print.

★ HANDS PERFORMANCE OTA, 1 GP: Security Check
They are the uncompromising protectors of airports: security check! Without them, the world would be in great danger. Bring it in an all black outfit with whatever gloves. Let's show everyone that you've got what it takes to keep our skies secure.

★ ARMS CONTROL OTA, 1 GP: Ramp agent
Ready to take control of the runway? With your on-the-beat moves and sharp lines, you'll be the one ensuring smooth flights for everyone. Your outfit should include fluorescent color.

★ LIP SYNC PERFORMANCE OTA, 1 GP: Holiday melancholy
You know the feeling of post-holiday blues. On your way back, you're listening to your favorite nostalgia playlist and thinking about your hot summer love. Bring it in your summertime outfit and play us the most heartfelt tune. 
! Send a song (mp3) of your choice for your 10s to house.of.ambtchs@gmail.com until May 25th !
Songs for lip sync battles: 
♪ Janet Jackson – Together Again
♪ Robyn – Dancing On My Own
♪ Rihanna – Love On Brain
♪ Sixpence None The Richer – Kiss Me

VOCABULARY:
OTA = open to all genders and identities
BQ = butch queens (cisgender gay/bi men)
FQ = femme queens (trans women)
TM = trans men
FF = female figures (trans women, drag queens, cisgender women)
MF = male figures (cis men, drag kings, trans men)
NB = nonbinary and gender nonconforming
Beginner = everyone who is walking a specific category under a year and never won

♡ If you (as a contestant or spectator) have any questions please contact us on our instagram @kikihouseofambitchous or by email house.of.ambtchs@gmail.com.

Lebanon Hanover embody modern romanticism and admire Wordsworth, art nouveau, British nature, and Berlin urbanism. Their ice-cold reply to an alienated world resonates with Selofan's experimental music, blending dreamy saxophone melodies, strong drum beats, and haunting vocals in emotionally striking live performances.

Tickets - bit.ly/FUCHS2_LIVE_LEBANON_HANOVER_SELOFAN
ad_creative_link_descriptions:
NOSTALGIA IS NEGATION. SADNESS IS REBELLION.

𝗟𝗲𝗯𝗮𝗻𝗼𝗻 𝗛𝗮𝗻𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿
An ice cold reply to the alienated world coming from two warm beating hearts. The duo of Larissa Iceglass and William Maybelline appear as true romantics of the modern age, admiring William Wordsworth, fascinated by the beauty of art nouveau aesthetics, exploring British seashores and forests at night as well as inspired by the urbanism of Berlin.

lebanonhanover.bandcamp.com

𝗦𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗳𝗮𝗻
Death-inspired love story by the Athens-based duo Selofan. From the beginning, they have created their own musical environment offering us a glimpse into ii to become overwhelmed by the emotional intensity of thier sound and words. Selofan avoid the comfort of settling into one sound and style – they keep experimenting. Dreamy saxophone melodies find their way through strong drum machine beats, a new wave riff, and powerful haunted female vocals, presenting themselves in such a theatrical wave, that each love performance is emotionally striking. 

selofan.bandcamp.com/

“You can experience life fully only when you’re completely free. That’s why the main ethos of VESELKA is freedom in all its expressions. You can dance, take your clothes off, stare — do whatever you desire, as long as you’re respectful of other people. ”Stas Tweeman, musician and founder of VESELKA in an interview for @calvertjournal. 

EVENT link in bio, presale on @resident_advisor & @gooutcz.

“VESELKA (rainbow in Ukrainian) was founded in Kyiv in 2018 as a safe space for queer and open-minded people. From the first episode, club kids found a place where they could express themselves and be free without any judgment. The mission of VESELKA is to spread equality, tolerance, and freedom for open-minded people through the power of rave,” says the founder of VESELKA Stanislav Tweeman.
